<!--             Magic weapons             -->
	
	<element name="Sayafushi" type="Magic Item" source="HB Content" id="ID_HBC_MAGIC_ITEM_SAYAFUSHI">
		<description>
			<p>Sayafushi's blade is too sharp and its edge is too smooth; it never chips or scratches from use, and blood slides off it immediately. Because of this, no sheath can hold it.</p>
			<p class="indent"><strong><em>First Sword.</em></strong> You have a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon, which deals an additional 1d8 slashing damage on a hit. Damage dealt with this weapon ignores resistance to slashing damage. If you are a spellcaster, you can use this weapon as a spellcasting focus.</p>
		</description>
		<setters>
			<set name="keywords">Katana</set>
			<set name="category">Magic Weapons</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">0</set>
			<set name="type" addition="katana">Weapon</set>
			<set name="rarity">Rare</set>
			<set name="attunement">true</set>
			<set name="enhancement">2</set>
			<set name="weapon">ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_GROUP_KATANAS</set>
		</setters>
	</element>

	<element name="Blade of Chaos" type="Magic Item" source="HB Content" id="ID_HBC_MAGIC_ITEM_BLADE_OF_CHAOS">
		<description>
			<p>The Blades of Chaos are a pair of chained blades fashioned by the God of War, Ares. You have a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic scimitar, which deals an additional 1d8 fire damage on a hit.</p>
			<p class="indent"><strong><em>Chaotic Pair. </em></strong>Blades of Chaos are always created in pairs and are intended to be used as such. If you are attuned to a pair of Blades of Chaos, which only requires one attunement slot, they both have the reach property and the thrown property with a normal range of 20 feet and a long range of 60 feet. When you throw this weapon, you can use a bonus action to pull it back into your hand.</p>
		</description>
		<setters>
			<set name="keywords">scimitar</set>
			<set name="category">Magic Weapons</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">0</set>
			<set name="type" addition="scimitar">Weapon</set>
			<set name="rarity">Rare</set>
			<set name="attunement">true</set>
			<set name="enhancement">1</set>
			<set name="weapon">Scimitar</set>
			<set name="weapon">ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_GROUP_SCIMITARS</set>
		</setters>
	</element>

	<element name="Mighty Marakas" type="Magic Item" source="HB Content" id="ID_HBC_MAGIC_ITEM_MIGHTY_MARAKAS">
		<description>
			<p>This pair marakas created from the power of the Great Tree of the Feywild harnesses the power of a goliath. This marakas are an inseparable pair, needing to be wielded together.</p>
			<p>This marakas have a bonus +1 on damage and attack rolls.</p>
			<p class="indent"><strong><em>Parry.</em></strong>  As a reaction you create a magical shield in the air, reducing the damage of a meelee attack by 1d8 + CON modifier.</p>
			<p class="indent"><strong><em>Goliath's Will (Once/rest).</em></strong>Shaking your marakas you call upon the power of the goliath in them giving you the following bonuses for 1 hour: You grow 2 sizes larger (alongside your items); You gain imunity to being charmed, frightned, paralized and stunned; You STR and CON is raised by 2 and your AC is raised by 3; You gain advantage on STR and CON saves.</p>
		</description>
		<setters>
			<set name="keywords">Maraka</set>
			<set name="category">Magic Weapons</set>
			<set name="cost" currency="gp">0</set>
			<set name="type" addition="maraka">Weapon</set>
			<set name="rarity">Legendary</set>
			<set name="attunement">true</set>
			<set name="enhancement">1</set>
			<set name="weapon">ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_GROUP_MARAKAS</set>
		</setters>
	</element>

